modules.description: Handles the conversion of `Pp.t` values to and from a stable intermediate representation, enabling reliable serialization and deserialization of pretty-printing structures. Works directly with `Pp.t` and a corresponding stable type that mirrors its structure. Useful for storing or transmitting formatted documents in a consistent binary or persisted form.

This module defines infix operators for composing `Pp.t` values, specifically providing the `(++)` operator to concatenate two pretty-printing documents. It works directly with the `Pp.t` type, which represents structured pretty-printing layouts. Use this module to build complex output formats in a readable, compositional way, such as generating aligned code or structured text output.
